[
    {
        "content": "<p>I think so! At least until method-style function calls land in Roc, but possibly even after that. I've seen it mentioned several times that <code>|&gt;</code> (also known as the pipe operator, or jokingly pizza <span aria-label=\"pizza\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f355\" role=\"img\" title=\"pizza\">:pizza:</span>) can/should be removed from Roc with WSA, but I'm skeptical of that. Since it's one of Roc's most recognizable operators (and personally one of my favorite elements of its syntax), I'd like us to fully reconsider it (and its family of related operators like <code>.</code>) in the context of the syntax changes coming this year.</p>\n<p>I think pipe shines best in multi-line pipelines. Here's an example I've used in previous topics...</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">main!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"s2\">\"./input.txt\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Path</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">from_str</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">try</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Path</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">read_bytes!</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">try</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Foo</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">from_bytes</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">transform</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Much</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">try</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Foo</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">to_bytes</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Path</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">write_bytes!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Path</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">from_str</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"./output.txt\"</span><span class=\"p\">))?</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Stdout</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">line!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"🥳 See ./output.txt\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>to ask about how we expect multi-line function call chains might look when method-style function calls land with static dispatch in several months after the compiler rewrite:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">main!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"s2\">\"./input.txt\"</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Path</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">from_str</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">read_bytes!</span><span class=\"p\">?</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Foo</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">from_bytes</span><span class=\"p\">)?</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">transform</span><span class=\"p\">)(</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Much</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">to_bytes?</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Path</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">write_bytes!</span><span class=\"p\">)(</span><span class=\"no\">Path</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">from_str</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"./output.txt\"</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"no\">Stdout</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">line!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s2\">\"🥳 See ./output.txt\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>It seems that <code>.(local_fn)</code> (also known as the \"pass to\" syntax) could be a one-to-one replacement for most pipes. However, I'm unclear whether folks want <code>.(local_fn)</code> to be that ubiquitous, and suspect that there are many circumstances where having a non-method-style function chaining syntax is desirable.</p>\n<p>Does anyone have an example of PNC+SD code that feels better as PNC+SD+<span aria-label=\"pizza\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f355\" role=\"img\" title=\"pizza\">:pizza:</span>?</p>",
        "id": 499334547,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1739396827
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The main problem is precedence, how do you make <code>|&gt;</code> work with method calls in a way that doesn't look weird?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">data</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">start</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">call</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">local_func</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">next_method</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 499336589,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1739397635
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You'd have to make a space-based operator bind the same as dots</p>",
        "id": 499336794,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1739397714
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><del>Also, the current plan is for <code>.method().other()</code> to act as sugar for <code>|x| x.method().other()</code></del> (from an old example)</p>",
        "id": 499336946,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1739397772
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I will agree that from an Elm/FP-in-general background, I much prefer the reading of <code>|&gt;</code> over the <code>.(local_func)(args)</code> thing</p>",
        "id": 499337059,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1739397819
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>With the recent whitespace discussions, we could make <code>|&gt;</code> always add newlines to the whole chain, turning the above to</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">data</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">start</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">call</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">local_func</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">next_method</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 499337257,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1739397905
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Which I believe is less confusing</p>",
        "id": 499338053,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1739398232
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I realize I may be in the minority on this, but I really like being able to do:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">time</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hours</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ago!</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>and I like that a lot better than</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">time</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hours</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ago!</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 499341565,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1739399775
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm not a big fan of <code>.(fn)(arg)</code> but I don't have a great alternative idea either</p>",
        "id": 499341660,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1739399828
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I do like <code>.</code> being the consistent chaining/autocomplete character, and I do like the precedence being more straightforward and easy to understand</p>",
        "id": 499341747,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1739399881
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If it weren't even more parens, I'd like it more</p>",
        "id": 499342230,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1739400116
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But the alternatives we discussed weren't great either</p>",
        "id": 499342283,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1739400128
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm considering throughout these discussions that most function chains should be methods anyway</p>",
        "id": 499342323,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1739400155
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So all these examples with |&gt; or <code>.(func)</code> are good at showing how these would look when used in volume</p>",
        "id": 499342376,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1739400185
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But they inflate the perceived frequency of these tools</p>",
        "id": 499342426,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1739400204
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>to be fair though, I'm also not a fan of multi-arg PNC with pipe:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Haskell\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">fn</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">arg1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">arg2</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>that super doesn't look like a function that is being passed 3 arguments <span aria-label=\"sweat smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f605\" role=\"img\" title=\"sweat smile\">:sweat_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 499342473,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1739400222
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and yet it is</p>",
        "id": 499342494,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1739400232
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'd say <code>val.method(arg1, arg2)</code> is the same thing, we're just used to it</p>",
        "id": 499342565,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1739400254
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But we're used to it so...</p>",
        "id": 499342635,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1739400293
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>fair!</p>",
        "id": 499342883,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1739400411
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but yes, I am used to it and it doesn't look weird to me <span aria-label=\"laughing\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f606\" role=\"img\" title=\"laughing\">:laughing:</span></p>",
        "id": 499342911,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1739400425
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"281383\">Richard Feldman</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/304641-ideas/topic/Do.20we.20still.20need.20.60.7C.3E.60.3F/near/499341565\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I realize I may be in the minority on this, but I really like being able to do:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">time</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hours</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ago!</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>and I like that a lot better than</p>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">time</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hours</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ago!</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I totally agree. I really like the <code>.()</code> syntax in general for local calls</p>",
        "id": 499352083,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1739405244
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>I'm not a big fan of <code>.(fn)(arg)</code> but I don't have a great alternative idea either</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I remember <code>.$</code> and <code>..</code> came up as options a couple times. <code>arg1..fn(arg2)</code>. Were they ever ruled out?</p>",
        "id": 499377631,
        "sender_full_name": "Sky Rose",
        "timestamp": 1739421191
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>.$</code> is getting some re-evaluation in <a class=\"stream-topic\" data-stream-id=\"304641\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/304641-ideas/topic/static.20dispatch.20-.20pass_to.20alternative\">#ideas &gt; static dispatch - pass_to alternative</a> , along with discussion of all alternatives for the method-style syntax version of <code>|&gt;</code></p>",
        "id": 499377832,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1739421347
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This seems like consensus to fully remove <code>|&gt;</code> by not implementing it in the new compiler.</p>",
        "id": 500490443,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1739905322
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For deprecation, I propose matching whatever is decided in <a class=\"stream-topic\" data-stream-id=\"316715\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/316715-contributing/topic/deprecating.20WSA.20.28whitespace.20application.20for.20function.20calls.29/with/499330548\">#contributing &gt; deprecating WSA (whitespace application for function calls)</a> but without any pre-<code>v0.1.0</code> PRs because the replacement syntax won't work before then.</p>",
        "id": 500490978,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1739905477
    }
]